LogicalColumn.name: Priority
LogicalColumn.Description: Priority of the problem reported on the service request

LogicalColumn.name: Area
LogicalColumn.Description: Area of the problem reported on the service request

LogicalColumn.name: Sub Area
LogicalColumn.Description: Subarea of the problem reported on the service request

LogicalColumn.name: Sub Area_I
LogicalColumn.Description: Language Independent version of Sub Area

LogicalColumn.name: Severity
LogicalColumn.Description: Severity of the problem reported on the service request

LogicalColumn.name: Sub Status_I
LogicalColumn.Description: Language Independent version of Sub Status

LogicalColumn.name: Billable Flag
LogicalColumn.Description: Denotes whether the service request is billable or non-billable

LogicalColumn.name: Entitlement Name
LogicalColumn.Description: Name of entitlement associated with the service request

LogicalColumn.name: Days Open
LogicalColumn.Description: "Number of days between service request close date and service request open date. If service request still open, then it is the number of days between data warehouse last refresh date and service request open date"

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: TIMESTAMPDIFF( SQL_TSI_DAY , "Oracle Data Warehouse"."Catalog"."dbo"."Dim_W_SRVREQ_D"."OPEN_DT", IFNULL("Oracle Data Warehouse"."Catalog"."dbo"."Dim_W_SRVREQ_D"."CLOSE_DT", VALUEOF("Warehouse Refresh Date"."LAST_REFRESH_DT")))

LogicalColumn.name: Days Open Category
LogicalColumn.Description: "Days Open Category by number of days open. Categories are, A: <= 5, B: 6 - 10, C: 11 - 15, D: 16 - 30, E: 31 - 45, F: 46 - 60 and G: 61+"

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprText: CASE WHEN "%1" IS NULL THEN 'A: <= 5' WHEN "%1" <= 5 THEN 'A: <= 5' WHEN "%1" <= 10 THEN 'B: 6 - 10' WHEN "%1" <= 15 THEN 'C: 11 - 15' WHEN "%1" <= 30 THEN 'D: 16 - 30' WHEN "%1" <= 45 THEN 'E: 31 - 45' WHEN "%1" <= 60 THEN 'F: 46 - 60' ELSE 'G: 61+' END
Expr.ExprTextDesc: CASE WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Open" IS NULL THEN 'A: <= 5' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Open" <= 5 THEN 'A: <= 5' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Open" <= 10 THEN 'B: 6 - 10' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Open" <= 15 THEN 'C: 11 - 15' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Open" <= 30 THEN 'D: 16 - 30' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Open" <= 45 THEN 'E: 31 - 45' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Open" <= 60 THEN 'F: 46 - 60' ELSE 'G: 61+' END

LogicalColumn.name: Price List
LogicalColumn.Description: Price list associated with the service request

LogicalColumn.name: Primary Symptom Code_I
LogicalColumn.Description: Language Independent version of Primary Symptom Code

LogicalColumn.name: Rate List
LogicalColumn.Description: Rate list associated with the service request

LogicalColumn.name: Reproducible
LogicalColumn.Description: Reproducibility of the problem reported on the service request

LogicalColumn.name: ROW_ID
LogicalColumn.Description: Row # of Service Request record in the database

LogicalColumn.name: Teller Type
LogicalColumn.Description: "Type of service handled by a Teller such a withdrawals, deposits, transfers etc."

LogicalColumn.name: Internal / External
LogicalColumn.Description: Denotes whether the service request originates internally or externally

LogicalColumn.name: Days Closed
LogicalColumn.Description: Number of days between service request close date and service request open date for all closed service requests

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprText: CASE WHEN "%1" IS NULL THEN 0.0d ELSE TIMESTAMPDIFF( SQL_TSI_DAY , "%2", "%1") END
Expr.ExprTextDesc: CASE WHEN "Oracle Data Warehouse"."Catalog"."dbo"."Dim_W_SRVREQ_D"."CLOSE_DT" IS NULL THEN 0.0d ELSE TIMESTAMPDIFF( SQL_TSI_DAY , "Oracle Data Warehouse"."Catalog"."dbo"."Dim_W_SRVREQ_D"."OPEN_DT", "Oracle Data Warehouse"."Catalog"."dbo"."Dim_W_SRVREQ_D"."CLOSE_DT") END

LogicalColumn.name: Days Closed Category
LogicalColumn.Description: "Days Closed Category by number of days closed. Categories are, A: <= 5, B: 6 - 10, C: 11 - 15, D: 16 - 30, E: 31 - 45, F: 46 - 60 and G: 61+"

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprText: CASE WHEN "%1" IS NULL THEN 'A: <=5' WHEN "%1" <= 5 THEN 'A: <= 5' WHEN "%1" <= 10 THEN 'B: 6 - 10' WHEN "%1" <= 15 THEN 'C: 11 - 15' WHEN "%1" <= 30 THEN 'D: 16 - 30' WHEN "%1" <= 45 THEN 'E: 31 - 45' WHEN "%1" <= 60 THEN 'F: 46 - 60' ELSE 'G: 61+' END
Expr.ExprTextDesc: CASE WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Closed" IS NULL THEN 'A: <=5' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Closed" <= 5 THEN 'A: <= 5' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Closed" <= 10 THEN 'B: 6 - 10' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Closed" <= 15 THEN 'C: 11 - 15' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Closed" <= 30 THEN 'D: 16 - 30' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Closed" <= 45 THEN 'E: 31 - 45' WHEN "Core"."Dim - Service Request"."Days Closed" <= 60 THEN 'F: 46 - 60' ELSE 'G: 61+' END
